This dataset contains data for the simulation of atomistic and coarse-grained (MOLC) water models.
The input molecular dynamics / coarse-grained molecular dynamics simulations data are written in the LAMMPS language. These input data contain information on: (1) the molecular geometry; (2) the topology and force fields; (3) the simulation protocol for the systems stabilization. The data are organized in the following subfolders:
1) atomistic. Input and geometry files for the atomistic systems studied (1000 molecules for each system), namely the Tip3P-Ew, SPC-E and Tip4P-05: 

  *.in file, the general input to be run in LAMMPS. It calls the following subfiles:

              - *.in.init, with the initialization simulation settings;
        
              - *.data file, with the geometry and topology for each system;
        
              - *.in.settings, with the force field definition for each model;
              - *.in.run, with the definition for the simulation run.

    *.lt file, Moltemplate file to generate the abovementioned files. This file calls the **.file in the forcefields folder (see below).


2) coarse. Input and geometry files for the MOLC coarse-grained systems studied (1000 molecules for each system), namely the Tip3P-Ew-CG, SPC-E-CG and Tip4P-05-CG:

    *.in file, the general input to be run in LAMMPS. It calls the following subfiles:

                - *.in.init, with the initialization simulation settings;
        
                - *.data file, with the geometry and topology for each system;
        
                - *.in.settings, with the force field definition for each model;
                - *.in.run, with the definition for the simulation run. In this file is also specified how to compute the thermodynamic properties in the MOLC coarse grained representation (temperature and pressure). 

    *.lt file, Moltemplate file to generate the abovementioned files. This file calls the **.file in the forcefields folder (see  below).


3) forcefields. Geometry, topology and force field definition for the atomistic and coarse-grained models:

     *.xyz file, generic geometry file for atomistic models;
     *_aa_01.lt, geometry, topology and force field for atomistic models, to be called by the *.lt file contained in the atomic folder for the definition of the LAMMPS input files;
     *_cg_01.lt, geometry, topology and force field for coarse grained models, to be called by the *.lt file contained in the atomic folder for the definition of the LAMMPS input files.

